---
title: Braised Birria-Style Beef Tacos 2x the delicious portions!
description: Birria is a flavorful Mexican stewed beef that’s perfect for loading into tortillas (which are perfect for a hungry crowd!). You’ll slow-cook beef with onions and potatoes, then serve it alongside tortillas, radishes, sour cream, cilantro, and lime wedges, family style, so everyone can build their own tacos. Get that braising broth on the table for dipping and drizzling—it’s the best part!

*This recipe is double the typical servings, providing 4 servings and 8 servings for a 2 person and 4 person box respectively.*
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/6668664dc08aa1c328e1a901-114bc9bc.jpeg
